The paper deals with the Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP) and its complexity, which is a central topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.CC). The paper also discusses the identification of classes of instances for which CSP can be solved in polynomial time, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
